dct_description_sm: Alternate title: Hamhung (Kanko), Korea. In upper left margin: Korea city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 5 meter contour interval and spot elevation. Korean names transcribed according to the McCune-Reischauer system. Japanese forms of Korean names (in parenthesis) transcribed according to the Modified Hepburn (Romaji) system. With a glossary. Relief shown by hachures, contours and spot heights. "Contour interval 5 meters." "Korean names transcribed according to the McCune-Reischauer system; Japanese forms of Korean names (in parentheses) transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) system." "Zone "C"." "6-45." Three classes of roads or trails, two classes of railroads, and areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Some buildings are named. Includes glossary to Korean, Japanese and English terms, inset map "Index to sources," and index "Key to precincts." Military grid. AMS 1.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
